    ## Basics
    {: #basics }

    There are two pieces required to implement a successful tooltip:

    {: .pco-demo-list}
    * Add the `has-tip` class to your element
    * Add a `data-tip` attribute with your tip text

  =code_sample_static
    a.has-tip href="#" data-tip="Imma tooltip." Tooltippin

  table.table
    tr
      td
        markdown:
          [Hover here](#){: class="has-tip" data-tip="SUCH TIPS!"}
      td
        =code_sample_static
          a.has-tip data-tip="SUCH TIPS!" Hover here
      td Default
    tr
      td
        markdown:
          [Hover here](#){: class="has-tip"}
      td
        =code_sample_static
          a.has-tip Hover here
      td
        markdown:
          no `data-tip` attribute warning
    tr
      td
        markdown:
          [Hover here](#){: class="has-tip" data-tip=""}
      td
        =code_sample_static
          a.has-tip data-tip="" Hover here
      td
        markdown:
          `data-tip` is blank. Tooltip should not fire.
          An empty `data-tip` attribute will prevent the tip from displaying.  This keeps empty tips from showing on generated or asyncronous views.

  

